programme.desc: Republic of Ireland v Serbia (Kick-off 7.45pm). Coverage of the Group D World Cup qualifier, which takes place at the Aviva Stadium. These two sides came into this batch of games as joint leaders of the group, so the outcome of this match could prove to be vital at the end of the qualifying campaign. The reverse fixture finished 2-2 last September, with Jeff Hendrick and Daryl Murphy scoring for Martin O'Neill's side

programme.desc: Documentary following an initiative to transform the lives of a group of young adults from Limerick through the power of sport, hoping that coaching them on the field will encourage them back into education. programme.title: A Sporting Chance
programme.desc: Liam Toland and Rosie Foley face an uphill struggle as they try to encourage their charges to commit to their training programme. In an attempt to boost morale, Munster Rugby invites the participants to an evening game, before Liam and Rosie ask them to write about their experience, with the two best essays winning their writers VIP tickets to watch Brian O'Driscoll play in his last home game for Ireland before retirement. Finally, the trainers organise a challenge game for their group, but the training programme hits a major setback when fights break out after the team is badly beaten
